## 6. Oversight Structure

**Dual oversight requirement**: This program operates under structurally separated oversight:

| Oversight Body | Responsibility | Review Cadence |
|---|---|---|
| [Technical Review Body — e.g., TSC] | Technical alignment, quality standards, infrastructure priority | Per quarterly review |
| [Governance/Compliance Body — e.g., OSC] | Charter compliance, budget adherence, transparency requirements | Per quarterly review |

Both bodies must agree on: participant selections, major renewals, terminations, and any proposed scope changes.

**Escalation path**: If the two oversight bodies disagree, the matter is escalated to the issuing governance authority for resolution. The operator does not resolve oversight disagreements unilaterally.

