## 7. Renewal and Sunset

### Sunset Clause

This program expires on **[CHARTER EXPIRY DATE]**. It does not continue by default. Continuation requires affirmative renewal by the issuing governance authority.

### Renewal Conditions

At least **60 days** before expiry, the operator must submit a renewal proposal to the issuing governance authority including:
- Outcomes achieved against charter criteria (quantitative evidence required)
- Updated dependency audit results justifying continued program relevance
- Proposed scope for next charter period (may be same, narrower, or broader)
- Updated budget request
- Any proposed changes to program design or oversight structure

### Early Termination

This charter may be terminated early if:
- The operator fails to meet reporting requirements for two consecutive periods
- The operator allocates funds outside the authorized budget envelope
- Either oversight body passes a motion of no confidence
- The issuing governance authority passes a termination vote
- The program fails to meet critical KPI thresholds for two consecutive quarterly reviews despite a remediation plan

